The paper presents a visual analytics approach for analyzing high-dimensional event sequence data, which involves leveraging a predefined hierarchy of dimensions to computationally quantify the informativeness of alternative levels of grouping within the hierarchy at runtime. This approach is likely to be of interest to researchers in several sub-categories of computer science, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Databases (cs.DB), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
